d as the red rose was the symbol of the Lancastrians and the white rose was the symbol of the Yorks.","url":"https://www.history.com/topics/british-history/wars-of-the-roses","urlTitle":"History - Wars of the Roses","jurisdictionLevel":2}],"lifeSummary":"When Joane Kriton was born about 1396, in Dorset, England, her father, John Kriton, was 31 and her mother, Mrs John Kriton, was 31. She married John de Woley before 1434, in England, United Kingdom. They were the parents of at least 2 sons. She died in Broadbottom, Cheshire, England."},"et":{"about 1396–":"umbes 1396–Surnud","1396–Female":"1396–Surnud","1395–1461":"1395–1461","1450–1542":"1450–1542","1453–Male":"1453–Surnud","1366–Male":"1366–Surnud","1367–Female":"1367–Surnud","1455":"1455","1367":"1367","1366":"1366","1542":"1542","1453":"1453","1396":"1396","1450":"1450","1461":"1461","1395":"1395","BEF. 1434":"enne 1434","about 1396":"umbes 1396","about 1450":"umbes 1450","Broadbottom, Cheshire, England":"Broadbottom, Cheshire, England","England":"Inglismaa, United Kingdom","Dorset, England":"Dorset, England"},"fi":{"about 1396–":"noin 1396–Kuollut","1396–Female":"1396–Kuollut","1395–1461":"1395–1461","1450–1542":"1450–1542","1453–Male":"1453–Kuollut","1366–Male":"1366–Kuollut","1367–Female":"1367–Kuollut","1455":"1455","1367":"1367","1366":"1366","1542":"1542","1453":"1453","1396":"1396","1450":"1450","1461":"1461","1395":"1395","BEF. 1434":"ennen vuotta 1434","about 1396":"noin 1396","about 1450":"noin 1450","Broadbottom, Cheshire, England":"Broadbottom, Cheshire, England","England":"Englanti, Yhdistynyt kuningaskunta","Dorset, England":"Dorset, England"},"fr":{"about 1396–":"environ 1396–Décédée","1396–Female":"1396–Décédée","1395–1461":"1395–1461","1450–1542":"1450–1542","1453–Male":"1453–Décédé","1366–Male":"1366–Décédé","1367–Female":"1367–Décédée","1455":"1455","1367":"1367","1366":"1366","1542":"1542","1453":"1453","1396":"1396","1450":"1450","1461":"1461","1395":"1395","BEF. 1434":"avant 1434","about 13